Unfortunately we will not be able to cover the replacement of the prop shaft as the boot is torn, which allowed grease to escape, foreign contaminants to enter, and ultimately require the replacement of the prop shaft. We do not cover torn rubber boots on our contracts. However, the customer's contract does cover them for the timing cover reseal and the replacement of the seals for the front transfer case. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees, fluids and shop supplies, as well as a $100 deductible. The payout is as follows:

Parts-102.23
Labour-$3430.70 (20.3 hours x $169/h)
Deductible-$100.00
PST-$240.15
GST-$176.65
Authorization-FKQUWLSXZ4

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.

Best regards, 


Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster
